    <annotation>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="EN">
                <position place="head" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>An act, sumwhat like that heroical aduenture of those thre worthyes, that brake thorowgh the army of the
                    Philistins, to fett Dauid water, being very dry.</marginalia_text>
                    <person name="King David"/>
                    <person name="Philistines"/>
                </position>
            </language>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="EN">
                <position place="left_margin" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>Desperate bowldnes. What other remedy, in extremity?</marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="left_margin" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>Audaces Fortuna juuat: quasi Miraculo diuino.</marginalia_text>
                    <person name="Fortuna"/>
                    <X-ref person="Virgil" book_title="Aeneid" language="LA" text="Audaces Fortuna iuuat"/>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>"Fortune favours the bold": as if a divine miracle.</translation>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="EN">
                <position place="left_margin" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>Lett there appere A famous difference betwene [the] lernid &amp; vnlernid imployed man:
                    aswell in exceding Industry, &amp; Zeale; as in pra[e]sent resolution, &amp; incomparable Cunning.</marginalia_text>
                    <emphasis method="pen" type="straight" text="[the] lernid"/>
                    <emphasis method="pen" type="straight" text="&amp; vnlernid"/>
                    <emphasis method="pen" type="straight" text="imployed"/>
                    <emphasis method="pen" type="straight" text="Industry"/>
                    <emphasis method="pen" type="straight" text="resolution"/>
                </position>
            </language>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>Ad fortia qua[e]q[ue] Acta, ferri oportet fortiss[im]a Imaginatione: sic Dauid, Goliam aggressus, statim
                    belluam prostrauit. H&icirc;c, ant&egrave; omnia, vel maxim&egrave; opus pra[e]senti, et confidentiss[im]a Resolutione.</marginalia_text>
                    <person name="King David"/>
                    <person name="Goliath"/>
                    <emphasis method="chalk" type="straight"/>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>Towards whatever courageous acts, it ought to be produced with the strongest imagination. Thus David, having attacked
            Goliath, at once knocked down the brute. In the present circumstances, before everything, or especially perceive the work beforehand, and with the most confident
            resolution.</translation>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian" anchor_text="brake through the warde of their ennemies">
            <language ident="EN">
                <position place="intext" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>A lusty braue escape.</marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
        </marginalia>
        
